I made a trigonometry
mistake in the first book,

00:12:49.880 --> 00:12:53.580
and it's really embarrassing,
because like anybody

00:12:53.580 --> 00:12:56.990
who knows some basic
trigonometry looks at that

00:12:56.990 --> 00:12:59.410
and they're like, no.

00:12:59.410 --> 00:13:02.400
It's in Kvothe's first
admission interview,

00:13:02.400 --> 00:13:05.770
and he answers with such
authority that a lot of people

00:13:05.770 --> 00:13:08.400
are like, I guess you're
right, and they move on.

00:13:08.400 --> 00:13:09.980
And I did the math
once, but then I

