you grow a beard like that?

01:00:53.200 --> 01:00:55.048
Do people ask you?

01:00:55.048 --> 01:00:56.552
AUDIENCE: Sometimes.

01:00:56.552 --> 01:00:59.392
PAT ROTHFUSS: And the
thing, I started saying,

01:00:59.392 --> 01:01:04.940
for two hours a day I sit in a
dark room and I just grow it.

01:01:07.510 --> 01:01:09.910
Because it's the
only way I can not

01:01:09.910 --> 01:01:13.760
be snarky about that
conversation anymore.

01:01:13.760 --> 01:01:18.600
This is what a person looks
like when they do not care.

01:01:18.600 --> 01:01:21.750
Don't ask me for
grooming suggestions,

01:01:21.750 --> 01:01:24.830
what the hell's wrong with you?

01:01:24.830 --> 01:01:28.350
This is man in
his natural state.

01:01:28.350 --> 01:01:31.470
I literally, I was going
to get a haircut for this,

01:01:31.470 --> 01:01:34.720
we scheduled a haircut, and
then the one person I trust

01:01:34.720 --> 01:01:38.310
to cut my hair, her kid got sick
the day before I was flying,

01:01:38.310 --> 01:01:40.270
I couldn't find
another haircut person,

01:01:40.270 --> 01:01:42.490
so you get to see
me in my full glory.

01:01:42.490 --> 01:01:48.020
I think it's been a year since
I've been trimmed in any way.

01:01:48.020 --> 01:01:55.330
This is not a maintenance
issue, I do not, beard.

01:01:55.330 --> 01:01:57.700
MALE SPEAKER: No favorite
comb or anything like that.

01:01:57.700 --> 01:01:58.408
PAT ROTHFUSS: No.

01:02:00.810 --> 01:02:03.170
